  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":4,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":13,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Reade was born in 1211, in Chichester, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Rede, was 38 and his mother, Ann Menis, was 26. He married Cecilia Randall before 1240, in Chichester, Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1234, in his hometown, at the age of 23, and was buried in Chichester, Sussex, England."},"et":{"1211–1234":"1211–1234","1213–Male":"1213–Surnud","1215–1300":"1215–1300","1230–1300":"1230–1300","1231–1264":"1231–1264","1173–1211":"1173–1211","1185–1280":"1185–1280","1231":"1231","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1240":"1240","1185":"1185","1173":"1173","1280":"1280","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1213":"1213","1234":"1234","1300":"1300","1211":"1211","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England","Chichester, Sussex, England":"Chichester, Sussex, England","Chichester, West Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Chichester, 